		<div class="comment_text"><p>In total agreement for the 50 minute thing both in health and mental ability to climb back on the horse. Part of my stairmaster is not good is that it uses these hydrolic cylinders to create resistance. When you start, you are at a given intensity; but, as the oil heats up (the things get wicked hot) I assume it lowers the viscosity and the intensity goes way up (less resistance == faster movement). As such, I hit a point where it simply gets too intense to continue.</p><p>I'd love to go the 50 minutes, but would need something with a variable resistance that can easily be controlled. All good machines should have this. Mine cost $70 and acts like a $70 machine :)</p><p>Time to invest in my cardiovascular health!</p></div>
